text: good morning from the Sunshine State the
orange state the peninsula state the
great southeastern state of Florida I
haven't been here since I was 15
so I'm beyond excited to spend all week
road-tripping around the state with
fresh eyes and new perspectives I'll
mostly be visiting less touristy places
apart from here Miami Beach's your
Disneyworld and your Florida Keys our
first stop takes us to a lovely region
called Charlotte Harbor more
specifically Punta Gorda and angle would
be CH on the western Gulf Coast after
spending the last two days here I am
absolutely stunned by what I am seeing
just amazing an abundance of wildlife
like alligators deer Panthers and birds
a coastline of untouched beaches with
white sand and crystal-clear seawater a
variety of national parks with views
like this and this a waterfront shopping
area called fisherman's village with
live music and tasty drinks a system of
mangroves that come in and out of the
water with jellyfish swimming around
incredible seafood like shrimp tacos
fresh lobster and tuna nachos and
sustainable towns like Babcock Ranch
which is America's first solar-powered
town more on that tomorrow I know it's
only been two days
but southwestern Florida is truly one of
a kind and I can't wait to see what else
there is to discover
I'm Drew Pinsky and if you like my
travel videos please click Subscribe and
join me as I plan to visit every country
in the world
